            <title>[KAFKA-19760] RecordTooLargeExceptions in group coordinator when offsets.topic.compression.codec is used</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-19760</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The coordinator runtime can be overly optimistic about compression ratios when filling up batches and can often overflow `max.message.bytes` of the topic. When this happens, all the group coordinator requests that wrote to the batch fail with an UNKNOWN_SERVER_ERROR. This error is non-retriable and disruptive to client applications.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
